headline: Cognition AI to buy Windsurf, doubling down on AI-driven coding
summary: The deal follows Google's $2.4 billion deal with Windsurf last week aimed at acquiring top talent and securing licensing rights to its technology.  The deal with Google marks a win for Windsurf's backers, who have raised $243 million from investors including Kleiner Perkins, Greenoaks, and General Catalyst, and was last valued at $1.25 billion one year ago, according to PitchBook.

headline: Moonvalley raises $84 million to bolster AI video tools
summary: Artificial intelligence research company Moonvalley has raised $84 million more in a funding round led by existing investor General Catalyst, it said on Monday, a week after releasing its first video AI model. WHY IT'S IMPORTANT Tech heavyweights including OpenAI and Alphabet are looking to get a leg-up in the lucrative entertainment industry, as film studios seek to use generative AI to speed up content creation and cut costs. But video and image generation tools have also led to lawsuits by major film studios against AI companies, accusing them of copyright infringement and plagiarism.
